The course covers the computer-assisted translation tools Wordfast, memoQ, SDL Trados Studio and Memsource, translation memories and termbases in different file formats as well as the opportunities and limitations of machine translation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to teach students to work with CAT tools and other technological aids, to analyze the different possibilities that translation software provides and the technical methods used for translation as well as to choose the most appropiate ways to solve problems related to translation technology.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course - is familiar with the basic principles of working with CAT tools; - knows the most common file formats used for translation technology; - is able to choose the appropriate technological tools and work methods for translation; - is able to analyze possible technical problems in the translation workflow and solve these problems according to their own knowledge and with the help of available information sources; - knows how to use the main features of CAT tools; - is able to create their own system of translation memories and termbases, managing it according to the most adequate principles for this system.
